Context: The Centre for Equitable Library Access (CELA) at George Brown College offers accessible library services for students with print disabilities. They provide nearly 400,000 accessible titles in various formats including Daisy text, Daisy Audio CDs, braille, downloadable audio and ebraille, and described movies. Some of the collections include business, health, culinary arts, disability studies, career/job seeking resources, award winners and best sellers, and more than 50 periodicals. Students can access materials using the given contact information: phone number - 416-415-2000; TTY - 1-877-515-5559; email - ask.george@georgebrown.ca. The website content is subject to change without notice and it should not be considered as a representation, offer or warranty. Students are responsible for verifying George Brown College fee requirements.
